{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b5aac93-0583-4400-b319-79c003ae0a09","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update base images\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck for breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0affa029-b54e-4025-80bf-2c403e3ba54c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":312,"requestId":"CFC1:119996:1861D35:1BCBA85:69E821CF"},"id":"8bcd405e-ba00-4609-9962-8e1f81246bfd","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:18:13.660Z","parentId":"fe121e43-60d2-42b7-9987-c33df2f56dea"}
